-- Peruvian Bank Loans Outstanding Rose 16% in November, Group Says
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2011-12-19T17:17:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/peruvian-bank-loans-outstanding-rose-16-in-november-group-says.html
Peru’s outstanding bank loans rose
16 percent in November from a year earlier, the Andean country’s
banking association said.  Outstanding loans totaled 125 billion soles ($46.3 billion)
as of Nov. 30, the association known as  Asbanc  said today in an
e-mailed statement. The total was 1.4 percent higher than a
month earlier.  Peruvian banks’ loan delinquency rate fell seven basis
points, or 0.07 percentage point, to 1.52 percent, Asbanc said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
